# ECZ EoC Syllabus Spec (every subject)

One JSON per subject under `data/curriculum/ecz-eoc/`, conforming to `EczSubjectSpec`. Shared code in `lib/ecz/eoc/` is **subject-agnostic** — never fork per syllabus.

## Reusable API

- `resolveEoc(spec, topicTag, taskType?)` — topic → taskType → unverified
- `requiresTaskType(spec, topicTag)` — UI picker helper
- `validateQuestion(spec, raw)` — structural then semantic
- `generateEczQuestion({ spec, topicTag, taskType?, … })` — resolve → generate → repair once
- `loadEocSpec` / `loadAllEocSpecs` — auto-discovers all JSON files
- `ECZ_SUBJECT_REGISTRY` / `loadSyllabusTopics` — all Assessment Scheme subjects ↔ ingest syllabus topics

## Canonical examples

- Maths I `mathematics-i-2021.json` (topic-mode)
- Agri `agricultural-science-4018.json` (topic + taskType)
- Art & Design `art-and-design-5012.json`
- Physics / Chemistry / Biology / Geography also shipped

Topic corpus: `ingest/extracted/syllabus/` (not the empty `Syllabus/` folder). Assessment source: `Validation_folder/`.

## Rules

- Never invent EoCs/marks/Bloom ranges absent from the Assessment Schemes PDF.
- Never prompt the model with a bare topic — resolve EoC first; stamp `taskType` when `resolutionMode` is `taskType`.
- Register new subjects in `subjectRegistry.ts` and drop the JSON under `data/curriculum/ecz-eoc/`.
